My visual data story

Introduction

This project explores cafe behaviours using observational data. We focus on coffee types, seating patterns, and how time of day affects customer behaviours.

Most Popular Coffee Types

Bar plot of coffee types

This plot shows the top coffee orders across observed cafes. Cappuccinos were the most popular.

Time Spent by Seating Type

Boxplot of time spent by seating type

We see indoor seats tend to lead to longer stays. Outdoor or takeaway orders had shorter duration.

Alone vs Group: Average Time

Bar plot of average time alone vs group

The average time spent at cafes varies based on whether individuals are alone or in a group. People in groups tend to stay longer on average, while those who visit alone spend a shorter amount of time.

Time of Day and Visit Duration

This final plot uses the actual Timestamp to look at how visit length changes throughout the day. Mid-morning and early afternoon have longer average duration.

Conclusion

This observational logging reveals trends in coffee culture. Visit duration and behaviour differ by coffee type, seating, and time of day.
